news.title: Jantri rates to jump in Ahmedabad's west
news.para: The deals being examined are located within the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) and Ahmedabad Urban Development Authority (AUDA) areas.

news.title: East Singhbhum DC seeks Rs 744.70 crore lease rent dues from Tata Steel
news.para: The DC said the administration has calculated the lease rent for a period of 23 years (1999-2022) for commercial use. The letter, dated 20 January 2023, mentions that the total due payable amount includes rent, cess, interest, and salami.

news.title: Haryana residents ready for battle against multi-storey floors in HSVP sectors
news.para: A decision in this regard was taken on Saturday by all the Residents Welfare Associations (RWAs) and Citizens Welfare Associations of Panchkula that had gathered under the banner of Haryana State HUDA Sectors Confederation (HSHSC), an umbrella organization.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Gujarat housing board, builder spar over redeveloped society
news.para: The bone of contention in the redevelopment is the sale of 48 flats from the 279 units in the complex. GHB recently released an auction notice for these 48 flats, claiming them as theirs under the agreement.

news.title: Cidco issues notice to Bhumiraj Builders over Parsik hill cutting
news.para: ​Meanwhile, a joint site survey was conducted by Cidco, NMMC, MPCB, Forest and Police and a report was submitted to HRC, citing the breaching of conditions in the leave and license agreement between Cidco and the developer.

news.title: With double digit CAGR, country's paint industry to reach Rs 1 lakh crore size
news.para: Roughly 50% of India’s paint industry is held by a handful of large corporate companies, and the balance is shared by about 2500 small and medium-scale companies having regional footprints.

news.title: UltraTech Cement's net profit falls 37.9% to Rs 1,062.6 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: However, its revenue from operations was up 19.53 per cent to Rs 15,520.93 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 12,984.93 crore in the corresponding period of the last fiscal.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh provides account numbers of residents whose houses were demolished to HC
news.para: ​The court had asked for bank account nos. of such persons after it was told that the amount of interim compensation has not been deposited in their bank accounts as directed by the court.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad: Housing bodies warn of legal action over PCMC notice to disconnect water supply
news.para: The civic body had issued notices to a few housing societies to snap water connections for unpaid property tax by a few flat owners.

news.title: Coimbatore corporation to conduct special camps to mop up tax collection
news.para: An official from the revenue department said based on 5,46,611 property tax assessments, including around 50,000 commercial assessments, the civic body should collect around 351 crore.

news.title: Education minister says Odisha must ensure people get PMAY-G houses
news.para: He was referring to the Union rural development ministry allowing the state to enter data of 9.5 lakh new beneficiaries in the Awaas Plus portal, where the waiting list of eligible beneficiaries are made, in November last year after the portal was closed in 2019.

news.title: Nanded civic body submits Gunthewari records to ED
news.para: A total of 6,500 files under the Maharashtra Gunthewari Developments (regularisation, upgradation and control) act 2001 were cleared and equal number of plots were regularised between September 2021 and January 2022.

news.title: Guwahati civic body yet to recover Rs 184 crore property tax
news.para: GMC mayor Mrigen Sarania said the civic body has been able to recover about Rs 84 crore property tax since it began the drive last month.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body to clear 170 pending building plan applications soon
news.para: The commissioner added that they will utilise the ward secretariat system to approach and alert the applicants over the shortfalls in their applications.

news.title: Ahmedabad: AFES issues notices to 350 buildings on fire NOCs
news.para: These buildings include hospitals, clinics, schools, and commercial and residential schemes. The managements of these buildings must renew their fire NOCs a month before these expire.
